[[File:Akathaso.jpg|thumb|An artistic rendition of an ''Akathaso'']]
'''''Akathaso''''' ({{lang-my|အာကာသစိုး}}) are Burmese ''[[nat (spirit)|nats]]'' (spirits) who inhabit the tops of trees and serve as guardians of the sky. ''Akathaso'' is derived from [[Pali]] ''akasa deva'' ({{my|အာကာသဒေဝ}}), which literally means "deity of the sky."{{sfn|MLC|1993}}

They are related to ''[[Yokkaso]]'' ({{my|ရုက္ခစိုး}}) and ''[[Bhummaso]]'' ({{my|ဘုမ္မစိုး}}), who respectively live on the trunks and roots of the trees. ''Bhummaso'' are guardian spirits of the earth while ''yokkaso'' are guardian spirits of trees.{{sfn|MLC|1993}}

