'''Albert Coppé''' (26 November 1911 in [[Bruges]] – 30 March 1999 in [[Tervuren]]) was a [[Belgium|Belgian]] and [[European Union|European]] politician and economist.

== Biography ==
Born in [[Bruges]] on 26 November 1911, Coppé was a founding member of the [[Christian Democratic and Flemish|CVP]] party and served in the [[European Commission]] as Commissioner for Social Affairs, Transport & Budget under the [[Malfatti Commission|Malfatti]] & [[Mansholt Commission|Mansholt]] Commissions. He also led an interim [[Coppé Authority|High Authority]] in the [[European Coal and Steel Community]] in 1967.

Coppé died in [[Tervuren]] on 30 March 1999.

