The '''Baron of Fonte Bela''' ({{lang-pt|Barão da Fonte Bela}}) was a title created by decree on 3 March 1836, confirmed by letter on 12 March 1836, by Queen [[Maria II of Portugal|Maria II]], in favour of [[Jacinto Inácio Rodrigues da Silveira]], a rich merchant and [[Liberal Wars|liberal]] politician from [[Ponta Delgada]], in the [[Portugal|Portuguese]] archipelago of the [[Azores]].

==List of barons==
# [[Jacinto Inácio Rodrigues da Silveira]], 1st Baron of Fonte Bela;
# [[Amâncio Gago da Câmara]], 2nd Baron and 1st [[Count of Fonte Bela]];
# [[Jacinto da Silveira Gago da Câmara]], 2nd Count of Fonte Bela;
# [[Jacinto Inácio da Silveira de Andrade Albuquerque Gago da Câmara]], 3rd Count of Fonte Bela.

After the installation of the Portuguese Republic, the monarchy was abolished, resulting in the transformation of [[Estevão Gago da Câmara]], into pretender to this title.

