{{Infobox radio station | image = virgin calgary new.png | image_size = 150px | name = CIBK-FM | airdate = September 6, 2002 | frequency = 98.5 [[MHz]] ([[FM radio|FM]]) | city = [[Calgary]], [[Alberta]] | format = [[Contemporary hit radio|Top 40 (CHR)]] | owner = [[Bell Media]] | licensee = [[Bell Media Radio]] G.P. | sister_stations = [[CKMX]], [[CJAY-FM]] | erp = 100,000 [[watt]]s | branding = 98.5 Virgin Radio | slogan = ''Calgary's #1 Hit Music Station'' | class = C | website = [http://www.iheartradio.ca/virginradio/calgary/ iheartradio.ca] | callsign_meaning = | coordinates = {{coord|51.065|N|114.214|W|type:landmark}} }} '''CIBK-FM''' is a [[contemporary hit radio|Top 40/CHR]] station based in [[Calgary]], [[Alberta]], Canada. The [[Bell Media]] outlet operates at 98.5&nbsp;MHz [[FM radio|FM]] with an [[effective radiated power]] of 100&nbsp;kW from a transmitter located at the intersection of Old Banff Coach Road and 85 Street Southwest, and studio located at CTV studios on Patina Rise.
CIBK is currently ranked #6 according to the Fall 2014 PPM Data report released by BBM Canada.<ref>[http://www.radiowest.ca/forum/viewtopic.php?f=46&t=19694 Fall 2014 Calgary PPM Ratings]</ref>
==History== The station received approval by the [[Canadian Radio-television and Telecommunications Commission|CRTC]] in 2001.<ref>[http://www.crtc.gc.ca/eng/archive/2001/DB2001-172.htm Decision CRTC 2001-172], ''CRTC'', March 12, 2001</ref> When CIBK made its debut on September 6, 2002 as ''Vibe 98.5'', they thought they would become the city's first [[R&B]]/[[hip hop music|hip hop]] outlet, but they were beaten to the punch by [[CJAQ-FM|CKIS]] (KISS 96.9) by about a month. This would spark a format war in Calgary, with both stations making potshots at one another. On April 1, 2003, CKIS would bail out and abruptly change to the [[Jack FM]] format, leaving CIBK as the victor.
However, CIBK would also go through an evolution of its own as they transitioned to a [[rhythmic contemporary]] direction by [[2003 in radio|2003]], and to their current mainstream top 40 direction by [[2004 in radio|2004]]. CIBK still played R&B/hip hop product (although at a reduced rate), and also incorporated [[pop music|pop]] and [[dance music|dance]] into the mix, in part due to its license with the CRTC that now requires the station to be programmed as a CHR outlet. Because CIBK was anticipated for years prior to its launch to be Calgary's long-awaited urban station, it had faced much criticism for bailing out to a Top 40 format leaving many of the station's hip-hop/R&B fans disappointed and let down by Standard.{{citation needed|date=November 2017}}
CIBK was part of the acquisition of most of the assets of [[Standard Broadcasting]] by [[Astral Media]] that was completed on October 29, [[2007 in radio|2007]]. Under Astral, CIBK dropped the rhythmic lean.
On April 1, 2010, [[Astral Media]] registered the domain names, VirginRadio985.com, Virgin985.com and VirginCalgary.com, which many speculated would be a branding change for CIBK to become a part of the ''[[Virgin Radio]]'' branding in Canada.<ref>[http://radioinsight.com/2010/04/27/a-virgin-coming-to-calgary/ Branding Change]</ref> This was confirmed on the Vibe Morning Show's June 23, 2010 broadcast, and the rebranding took place on June 30 at Noon,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vibe985.com/|title=Vibe 98.5 main page, "Tomorrow on The Vibe Morning Show"|date=June 23, 2010|accessdate=June 23, 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100209183250/http://www.vibe985.com/#|archive-date=2010-02-09|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref> and will retain its [[Top 40]] format. It is the second [[Virgin Radio]] station with a mainstream [[top 40]] format after [[Toronto]]'s [[CKFM-FM|CKFM]]. The last song to be played on "Vibe" was "[[Goodbye (Kristinia DeBarge song)|Goodbye]]" by [[Kristinia DeBarge]], while the first song on "Virgin Radio" was "[[California Gurls]]" by [[Katy Perry]].<ref>[http://calgary.virginradio.ca/broadcasthistory.aspx Virgin Radio's playlist]</ref><ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RLI8gFAj5LE</ref>
CIBK-FM is the longest-tenured [[contemporary hit radio|CHR]] station in [[Alberta]] still having the format today, only [[Edmonton]]'s [[CKNG-FM]] (now [[adult hits]] since [[2004 in radio|2004]]) had the longest-tenured format from [[1991 in radio|1991]]-[[2003 in radio|2003]].
As part of the merger of Astral and [[Bell Media]] approved by the [[Canadian Radio-television and Telecommunications Commission|CRTC]] on June 27, 2013, CIBK is now owned by Bell Media.
== Music format == Like most other Canada's Virgin Radio stations, CIBK brands itself as broadcasting "the most hit music" with 40 minutes of commercial free hit music each hour and it also broadcasts the extended version of this kind between 4:25 and 5:55 PM weekdays.
