'''''Doctrine and Life''''' is an [[Ireland|Irish]] religious periodical published by the [[Dominican Order|Dominican]] religious order. It was initially published from September 1946 as part of the ''[[Irish Rosary]]'' magazine. From February 1951 it was published as a separate periodical, under its founding editor Fr. Anselm Moynihan. From 1951 to 1961 it was published bimonthly, before becoming a monthly publication in January 1961. 

Prominent Irish priest Fr [[Austin Flannery]] became its second editor in 1957.

