{{for|the Turkish channel|Hayat TV (Turkey)}} {{Infobox Network |network_name = Hayat TV |network_logo = |country = [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]] |network_type = Broadcast Television Network |available = Worldwide Exclusively on BosnaTV IPTV |launch_date = 24 February 1992 |website = [http://www.hayat.ba Hayat TV website] }}
'''Hayat TV''' is a [[television]] station from [[Sarajevo]], [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]]. The word, "[[wikt:hayat|Hayat]]", means "life" in [[Arabic language|Arabic]].
It is a privately owned TV station, which started airing on 24 February 1992. Its coverage is over 1.5 million people in Bosnia, numerous cable subscribers in the neighbouring countries, and satellite viewers. In the beginning of 2009 Hayat TV opened its new headquarters in [[Vogošća]], suburb of [[Sarajevo]].
Hayat now consists of a "Hayat" channel for the Bosnia region and also a [[Hayat Plus]] channel for [[Bosnian diaspora|its diaspora]]. In early 2012 the channel opened two new music channels, [[Hayat Folk]] to cater for Bosnian folk music, and [[Hayat Music]] to cater for 50% English music, and 50% local pop music. Hayat Music became the first channel in Bosnia to be transmitted in [[widescreen]], [[16:9]] ratio. In 2014, Hayat opened first Bosnian channel for kids named [[Hayatovci]]. Hayat's logo bears resemblance to American TV network [[NBC]]'s distinct [[NBC logos|peacock logo]]. Hayat, along with [[Alternativna televizija|ATV]], 2011. founded Program Plus, part of the joint program that two televisions.
All 5 Hayat's channels transmits in Europe through [[EutelSat16]] satellite and various cable operators. The station also broadcasts all 5 of its channels worldwide exclusively on the BosnaTV IPTV platform - Hayat, Hayat Plus, Hayat Folk, Hayat Music and Hayatovci.
