{{Politics of Liechtenstein}}
'''General elections''' were held in [[Liechtenstein]] on 5 and 7 February 1982. The result was a victory for the [[Patriotic Union (Liechtenstein)|Patriotic Union]], which won 8 of the 15 seats in the [[Landtag of Liechtenstein|Landtag]]. Voter turnout was 95.4%, although only male citizens were allowed to vote.<ref>[http://www.ipu.org/parline-e/reports/arc/LIECHTENSTEIN_1982_E.PDF Liechtenstein] Inter-Parliamentary Union</ref>
